Abstract: Provides for the funding of the district public defender in the 19th Judicial
District Court.
Proposed law provides that, in addition to any funding provided by the office of the state
public defender, the district public defender's office for the 19th JDC is entitled to an
expense allowance for the salaries of certain staff and employees and an expense allowance
for certain expenses incurred in the discharge of their official duties.
Proposed law authorizes East Baton Rouge Parish to pay a sum of not less than $1,000,000
from its general fund for any of the items of expense incurred by the district public defender
when acting in his official capacity.
Proposed law relative to the authorized payments from East Baton Rouge Parish's general
fund for district public defender expenses terminates on July 1, 2028.
(Adds R.S. 15:161.1)
Summary of Amendments Adopted by House
The House Floor Amendments to the engrossed bill:
1. Authorize East Baton Rouge Parish to pay a sum of not less than $1,000,000
from its general fund for any expenses incurred by the district public defender
when acting in his official capacity.
2. Remove proposed law that requires the expenses of the district public defender
to be borne proportionately by the parish and each city, as determined by the
respective governing authorities.
3. Provide that the authorized payments from East Baton Rouge Parish's general
fund for district public defender expenses terminates on July 1, 2028.
4. Make technical changes.
